Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The property is a modern detached production/manufacturing building of steel frame construction with profile metal clad elevations under a pitched metal clad roof. Speke is located approximately 8.6 miles (13.8 km) south-east of Liverpool city centre on the north bank of the Mersey. The area is served by Speke Boulevard, (A561 dual-carriageway), which is the main southern gateway into Liverpool, as well as giving access to the M62 (via the A562 and A5300). The property is located in a very prominent position with frontage to Speke Hall Road, which is the principal route from Speke Boulevard (A561) to Liverpool John Lennon Airport. A Holiday Inn Express hotel is situated adjacent to the unit. Speke’s proximity to the communications network, ports and thriving workforce of Liverpool has allowed it to become a major industrial, manufacturing and business location for the North West of England. Local occupiers include Littlewoods, Dobbies Garden Centres, Classic Couverture, HBOS, DHL, National Blood Centre,
Riverside Housing Association as well as a 4-star Marriott hotel, David Lloyd Leisure Centre and New Mersey Shopping Park.

Triumph Business Park is a 60 acres (24.281 hectares) major storage / distribution / commercial environment strategically located close to Liverpool John Lennon Airport and comprises approximately 800,000 sq ft (74,322 sq m) of business space in a secure environment. The Park has 24-hour access with a security lodge and barrier at the entrance. Triumph Business Park Is located close to both the M62 & M56 motorways and less than 1 mile from Liverpool John Lennon Airport.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Prime Point will be situated on Goodlass Road, South Liverpool. Goodlass Road connects with the A5275 Speke Hall Road, which in turn connects with Speke Boulevard (A561) and provides excellent access to the M57 via the Knowsley Expressway and the M56.

Nearby key local amenities include the expanding Liverpool John Lennon Airport. M&S Simply Food, B&Q & Next amongst others. Triumph Business Park is located less than 1 mile from Liverpool John Lennon Airport and within 25 miles of Manchester International Airport.

Interchange 81 is immediately adjacent to J1 of M57 and J6 of the M62. Liverpool John Lennon Airport is 7 miles to the south and Manchester Ariport
is 28 miles to the south east. Liverpool Lime Street station and Runcorn station provide regular rail services to London Euston with services to Manchester, Warrington and Preston. Liverpool 2 Deep water container terminal is 15 miles to the north via the M57.

Central 23 is located in a prominent position on Carruthers Street, off Pumpfield Road and is a few metres from the junction with the A5038 Vauxhall Road. The site sits just 0.5 miles from Liverpool City Centre and only 15 minutes (4.6 miles) from the M62 motorway. The A5038 and surrounding roads offer fast access to the Liverpool Docks & L2 deep port, just 10 minutes (4 miles) to the north. The Wirral and M53 are accessed via the Kingsway tunnel just 4 minutes (1.3 miles) from the site. The location also offers excellent access to local amenities; Liverpool One Shopping Centre is 0.7 miles from the site, Moorfields Railway Station lies 0.5 miles to the south, with Liverpool Lime Street Station, the main station serving the city and
providing services to Euston, circa 1 miles to the south east.

Cables Trade Park is a new speculative development in a prominent location adjacent to Cables Retail Park. The site will comprise an industrial unit totaling 21,300 sq ft alternatively this can be split to provide 3 units at 7,000 sq ft, available to occupy in Q1 2022.

The units have been extensively refurbished to provide units from approximately 2,435 sq ft. Stonebridge Business Park East is located off Hermes Road with direct access to the East Lancashire Road (A580) via Electric Avenue, only 1 mile from Junction 4 of M57.
Stonebridge Business Park East is located on Electric Avenue with direct access to the East Lancashire Road (A580), only 1 mile from Junction 4 of M57.

Element at Alchemy Business Park comprises 3 no. detached new build industrial units situated in a highly prominent position fronting the A580 (East Lancashire Road) in Knowsley. 

Knowsley Industrial and Business Park is one of the largest employment areas in the UK comprising over 1,200 acres and is home to around 1,000 companies. Alchemy Business Park is prominently located fronting the A580 East Lancashire Road, less than 1 mile from junctions 4 and 5 of the M57 and 8.3 miles from the Port of Liverpool.

Knowsley Industrial and Business Park is one of the largest employment areas in the UK comprising over 1,200 acres and is home to around 1,000 companies. Alchemy Business Park is prominently located fronting the A580 East Lancashire Road, less than 1 mile from junctions 4 and 5 of the M57 and 8.3 miles from the Port of Liverpool.

Graylaw Trading Estate comprises a multi-let industrial scheme comprising 13 units. Each unit is steel portal frame construction with part brick/part clad elevations under a pitched clad roof incorporating translucent roolights. Each unit benefits from concertina loading doors as well as dedicated parking to the front, internal offices and W.C. and three phase electricity supply. Graylaw Trading Estate is an established estate in the Aintree industrial area of North Liverpool. Access to the estate is from Long Lane via Brookfield Drive and Wareing Road. Long Lane in turn links with both Ormskirk Road (A59) & the East Lancashire Road (A580) providing access to the M57, M58, linking with the M62 and M6. The estate is well established & other occupiers include the Royal Mail & NHS.

Haydock is considered one of North West’s premier Industrial locations due to its strategic connectivity situated at the intersection of the M6 (junction 23) and the A580 dual carriageway (East Lancs Road), almost midway between the cities of Manchester (18 miles) and Liverpool (16 miles). Nassau Business Park is located on Bahama Road off North Florida Road, within Haydock Industrial Estate an established industrial location with immediate access to the A580 East Lancs Road and Junction 23 (M6) within a 1.5miles. Major local occupiers include Amazon, Kelloggs, Costco and J.Sainsburys.

The property comprises a two bay single storey purpose built distribution warehouse. The property occupies a prominent position on Millfield Lane, the main road serving Haydock Industrial Estate that links the A580 East Lancashire Road to the south with the A58 Liverpool Road to the north. The property is accessed off Hall Wood Avenue and is adjacent to the two largest distribution warehouses on the estate occupied by Booker Wholesale (400,000 sq ft) and Sainsbury’s (626,000 sq ft). Other major occupiers on the estate include Costco, Palmer & Harvey, Corus and Syncreon.Haydock is in an established industrial / distribution location occupying a strategic position at the intersection of the A580 East Lancashire Road dual carriageway and Junction 23 of the M6 motorway. Located at the heart of the North West region’s motorway network, Haydock is approximately 15 miles east of Liverpool and 21 miles west of Manchester and benefits from excellent transport networks throughout the region. Haydock is a recognised location for major distribution facilities in the North West and is situated in St Helens Borough in Merseyside.

Haydock 60 is strategically located within the heart of Haydock Industrial Estate area and is accessible via the A580 East Lancashire Road which is within 1 mile of junction 23 of the M6. Ins addition the intersection of the M6 and M62 motorways is within 5 miles. Haydock is a recognised location for distribution facilities in the North West  and neighbouring occupiers include Palmer U& Harvey, Booker, Belmont,m The Book People and Costco.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Haydock Industrial Estate is strategically located within the heart of the Haydock Industrial area and is accessible via the A580 East Lancashire Road
which is within 1 mile of Junction 23 of the M6. Haydock is a recognised location for distribution facilities in the North West and neighbouring occupiers include Sainsbury’s, Booker Belmont and Costco. Haydock Industrial Estate was built in the 1970s and has subsequently been refurbished to provide an estate extending to 250,000 sq ft, comprising 32 industrial / warehouse units with potential for trade counter use. The locally managed units range from 3,000 to 30,000 sq ft and offer a range of specifications.

Hardstanding land in established prime industrial location. Links to regional and national arterial routes. Ideal for external storage or parking. Mains services (Electricity and water).

Centro Park is a modern, self-contained industrial park located on Beckett Close and is accessed directly off Gores Road. The units are of portal frame construction and provide flexible accommodation with ample loading and car park areas. Knowsley Industrial Park is the largest industrial park in Merseyside and is home to a host of major occupiers including News International, QVC, Exel, Sonae and Dams International. The park can be accessed from junctions 4 and 5 of the M57 which itself joins the M62, seven miles to the south. The East Lancs Road (A580) forms the southern boundary of the estate and provides quick access to Liverpool City Centre to the west and the M6 Motorway at Haydock, 10 miles to the east, with access at Junction 23.

Academy Business Park is situated in the heart of Knowsley Industrial Park, the principal logistics and industrial area within the Borough and the largest industrial area in the Liverpool City Region, home to over 600 businesses. Academy is located on one of the main arterial routed which connects Liverpool to Manchester. Junction 4 of the M57 is a three minute drive from the park allowing quick and easy access to the M62 and M6. Knowsley is a well-established business location that has attracted a wide range of companies such as QVC, Makro, Matalan and Vertex – along with leisure provider David Lloyd Health Clubs and Liverpool Football Club’s Academy, which adjoin the Academy Business Park site. Both Liverpool John Lennon Airport and Manchester Airport are within easy-driving distances, offering a full range of facilities for passengers and cargo transporters alike. The port of Liverpool
is just under 9 miles from the business park, where the £400m Liverpool2 scheme is set to provide north based exporters with a more competitive route to international markets. Academy Business Park is located on one of the main arterial routes which connects Liverpool to Manchester. Junction 4 of the M57 is a three minute drive from the park, allowing access to the M62 in under 10 minutes and M6 in just 15 minutes.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: 2 Full Height Electric Level Loading Doors

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: One of Merseyside’s most high profile sites, close to Switch Island where the M57 and M58 meet and within 2 miles of Liverpool2, the cities new Superport. Planning consent has now been granted, with construction of phase 1 of the scheme commencing shortly. The scheme will consist of 3 units of 12,000, 21,615 and 42,515 sq ft available on a leasehold basis. 36,000 sq ft has been pre-let to Selco and a 2 acre plot has been sold to Euro Garages for a Starbucks drive thru and petrol filling station. A further 4.5 acres is available for pre-let enquiries up to 90,000 sq ft.
